The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Sept. 13: Sebi today further tightened norms for foreign institutional investors (FIIs), which invest in the Indian securities market but do not disclose the proper identity of their sub-accounts. The regulator has made it mandatory for FIIs to disclose all information relating to the sub-accounts operated by them at the time of filing applications with the regulator and the Reserve Bank of India. 

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: In a partial win for Ranbaxy in the ongoing patent litigation with Pfizer over Atorvastatin (Lipitor), a district court in the Netherlands has ruled in its favour in one of the patents, while invalidating another. 

 Tokyo, Sept. 13: Nissan Motor will decide on a factory with Suzuki Motor in India within two months. Were in negotiations right now. Our decision will be within a month or two, vice-chairman Takeshi Isayama said. 

 New Delhi, Sept. 13: Gail (India) is likely to bid for at least one-third of the 55 oil and gas blocks offered under the sixth round of auction. We have been participating in the previous NELP rounds and will definitely put in strong bids this time too, Gail chairman and managing director S.P. Rao said.

 Mumbai, Sept. 13: Escorts will invest Rs 25 crore to set up a facility in Uttaranchal to manufacture auto components and railway equipment.




